You are here: SALESFORCE HELP
DOCS
INSURANCE
Upgrade Insurance

If you already use Insurance and you're ready to upgrade to a recent release, you're in the right place. Learn how to prepare and complete your upgrade so you can start using all the great features now available.

Upgrade Workflow
Complete Prerequisite Tasks
Plan Your Upgrade
Install packages:
Install Managed Packages for Insurance

Find the most recent package links in the Insurance Release Summary.

There isn't a new Unmanaged Package or Vlocity Installation Assistant Package for the Summer ’24 release. To upgrade your org to Summer ’24, the only thing to install is the Managed Package (or Packages).

Complete Installation Assistant Tasks Manually

There are specific steps for an Insurance org, and additional steps for orgs with the Insurance Industries Extension package.

NOTE If you're upgrading from Spring ’23, Summer ’23, Winter ’24, or Spring ‘24 to Summer ’24, and you completed the Installation Assistant tasks for the previous release, you can skip the Installation Assistant tasks for Summer ’24.

Complete Post-Upgrade Tasks
Plan Your Upgrade to Insurance
Before you upgrade, verify a few details about your current org and figure out exactly which release to upgrade to.
Package Installation Flows for Insurance Upgrades
Your release includes new managed packages. If you plan to use the Insurance Industries Extension package, you have two managed packages to install.

Complete Installation Assistant Tasks Manually
If you're upgrading from several versions back, you can simplify your upgrade by focusing on changes between releases and by completing certain tasks only one time.

Post-Upgrade Tasks for Insurance
To complete your upgrade, perform required post-upgrade tasks.
title: Upgrading Salesforce Insurance
